The 'libccll' is a helper library with full name 'library of common c-language in linux'.
It aims to wrap and aggergate the most-commonly function.

FUNCTION LIST:
  [config]
    1. ini config file parser.
       A light-weight ini-file and ini-text-in-memory parser.
       Get the value from specify section and key.

  [common]
    1. memory alloc
       Wrap the malloc&free, track memory allocated to help avoid memory leaks.
       It's highly recommanded to replace the traditionaly malloc&free.
 
    2. types definition
       Import the boolean type.
       Import the container_of.

    3. text process
       Wrap the 'read-line' from text.
  
    4. delay
       Wrap the sleep function to marco.

  [event]
    1. event publish system
       An event publish and subscribe system.

  [log]
    1. log wrapper
       Standardize the log output.

  [queue]
    1. List
       A doubly linked list.

  [system]
    1. shell executer
       Execute shell command and fetch the result.

    2. timer
       Just a timer, wrap with 'timerfd'.

